  "passageParts": [
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": "There are many understandable reasons why you might find it difficult to ask for help when you need it. Psychologists have been interested in this\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 1
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nfor decades, not least because people’s widespread\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 2
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nto ask for help has led to some high - profile failures. Asking for help takes\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 3
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​. It involves communicating a need on your part—there’s something you can’t do.\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 4
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​, you’re broadcasting your own weaknesses, which can be\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 5
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​. You might worry about coming across as incompetent. You might have\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 6
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nabout losing control of whatever it is you’re asking for help with.\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 7
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nsomeone starts to help, perhaps they’ll take over, or get credit for your earlier efforts. Yet another\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 8
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nthat you might be worried about is being a nuisance or\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 9
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nthe person you go to for help. If you struggle with low self - esteem, you might find it especially difficult to\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 10
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nfor help because you have the added worry of the other person\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 11
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nyour request. You might see such refusals as implying something\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 12
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nabout the status of your relationship with them. To\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 13
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nthese difficulties, try to remind yourself that everyone needs help sometimes. Nobody knows everything and can do everything all by themselves. And while you might\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 14
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\ncoming across as incompetent, there’s actually research that shows that advice - seekers are\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 15
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nas more competent, not less. Perhaps most encouraging of all is a paper from 2022 by researchers at Stanford University, in California, that involved a mix of contrived help - seeking interactions and asking people to\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 16
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\ntimes they’d sought help in the past. The findings showed that help - seekers generally underestimate how\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 17
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nother people will be to help and how good it’ll make the help - giver feel (for most people, having the chance to help someone is highly\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 18
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\n). So, bear all this in mind the next time you need to ask for help.\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 19
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​, take care over who you ask and when you ask them. And if someone can’t help right now, avoid taking it personally. They might just be too\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 20
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​, or they might not feel confident about their ability to help."
    }
  ],
